The paper discusses bibliometric indicators and their validity in predicting successful researchers in astrophysics. While the paper is not directly related to computer science, it involves the use of data analysis and statistical methods, which are commonly used in computer science research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries), which deals with the organization, retrieval, and analysis of digital information. Other likely sub-categories include cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
